text: Rochester Cathedral is a Norman church in Rochester, Kent, and the cathedral of the Anglican diocese of Rochester. It was originally founded in 604 AD, and rebuilt by the Normans. The present church was consecrated in 1130. It became a place of pilgrimage after William of Perth was murdered nearby in 1201.Rochester Cathedral Official website of Rochester Cathedral == References == == Other websites == *Official website of Rochester Cathedral *A history of the King's School and of the choristers of Rochester Cathedral Category:Anglican cathedrals in England Category:Buildings and structures in Kent Category:12th-century buildings and structures
